    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tiered sleeve ruffles of lace or other cloth that serve as cuffs; fashionable especially during the late 17th century to the mid 18th century. Also, detachable undersleeves edged with lace or embroidery, fashionable during the middle of the 19th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
